I&#x27;m trying to upload my ssh publick key, but always with the same error message "Invalid file type".

I&#x27;ve followed bb ssh tutorial, generated new keys, changed chmod...

{{[dudko@archy ~]$ ssh -V OpenSSH_5.9p1, OpenSSL 1.0.0e 6 Sep 2011}}

At home, I can clone any repository, but at work, where there is a proxy, I can´t clone. The response is (in portuguese):

//"Nenhuma conexão pôde ser feita porque a máquina de destino as recusou ativamente"//

That in english is something like this:

//"No connection could be done because remote host refused it"//.

I used the following line to get this error:

*hg -v clone https://bitbucket.org/tidalwave/betterbeansbinding-src*

Feature request. Could you add this to your CSS file so that there is always a vertical scroll bar like on google.com. It makes the page jump less.

Thanks,

{{{\\
#!css

html { overflow-y: scroll; }\\
}}}
